CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, April 6, 1957, pg. 17 reads: "1. Top award in Clabber Girl Baking Powder cake-baking contest went to Mrs. Hattie Hickman, left. Mrs. Willie Harris, Mrs. Enna Majeed and Mrs. Lucille Davenport won second, third and fourth prizes.  Mrs. Hickman is the daughter of Mrs. Harris.  Looking on are J. Walter Carroll, national director of The Courier Home Service Fairs, and Mrs. Daisy E. Lampkin, vice president of The Courier."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of cake contest winners Hattie Hickman, Mrs. Willie Harris, Enna Majeed, and Lucille Davenport, standing in front of J. Walter Carroll and Daisy E. Lampkin in Syria Mosque for the 1957 Pittsburgh Courier Home Service Fair
